"""Ghost Agent CLI — a small, pretty streaming client for the whole agent.

Talks DIRECTLY to the agent's API (``/v1/chat/completions`` + ``/api/*``);
the key rides in the ``X-Ghost-Key`` header. Beyond chat it drives the
agent's real feature surface:

* **Rendered replies** — the stream is rendered live as Markdown (rich):
  headers, lists, tables, bold/italic, and syntax-highlighted code blocks.
* **Durable sessions** — every turn carries a ``session_id`` so the server
  persists the conversation; ``/sessions`` lists them and ``/resume``
  continues one from any device. (The old ``conversation_id`` field was
  never read by the agent and has been retired in favour of this.)
* **Real turn cancellation** — each request sends an ``X-Request-ID`` that
  keys the agent's turn registry, so Ctrl-C actually cancels the running
  turn server-side (releasing the global turn lock) instead of merely
  closing our socket while the agent keeps working. ``/turns`` shows
  what's running or queued; ``/cancel [hard]`` unwedges a stuck turn.
* **Operations** — ``/health`` (runtime introspection), ``/notify``
  (pending autonomous-activity notifications, watermark-acked),
  ``/memory fix|rm`` (surgical vector-memory corrections).
* **Files & workspace** — ``/upload``/``/download`` move files in and out
  of the sandbox; ``/save``/``/load`` snapshot and restore the whole
  workspace (chat + scratchpad + sandbox) as a zip.
* **Projects** — list/inspect/switch/resume/advance the agent's long-term
  projects and their task plans.

Also works one-shot for scripting: ``ghost -p "question"`` (or pipe stdin) —
raw text when piped, rendered when stdout is a terminal.
"""
